  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db4\u0dc5\u0db8\u0dd4 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db4\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dca\u0db4\u0dad \u0db1\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb \u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb 150\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db4\u0dd0\u0dbd\u0dca\u0db4\u0dad\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A commemorative postcard to mark 150 years since the first post in Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A special commemorative postcard was issued today (1) at the Parliament Complex to mark 150 years since the first postcard was issued in Sri Lanka.",
        "There, this commemorative postcard was presented to Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena by the Minister of Transport, Highways and Mass Media Mr. Acharya Bandula Gunawardena.",
        "Acharya Bandula Gunawardena, Minister of Transport, Highways and Mass Media said that 1000 of these special commemorative postcards will be issued and can be purchased at a price of 300 rupees.",
        "Sri Lanka's first postcard was issued on September 1, 1872, a two-cent stamp with a portrait of Queen Victoria.",
        "This special commemorative postcard has been issued with a photo of the first postcard in this country.",
        "Former Speaker Chamal Rajapakse, Members of Parliament Mudita Prashanthi Soysa, Dr. Gayashan Navanda, Yadamini Gunawardena, Secretary of the Ministry of Mass Media Anusha Palpita, Postmaster General Ranjith Ariratne and senior officials of the Postal Department were also present on this occasion."
      ],
